SIMPLE: several
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Several
<hw>Sev"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF., fr. LL.
<ets>separalis</ets>, fr. L. <ets>separ</ets> separate, different. See
<er>Sever</er>, <er>Separate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Separate;
distinct; particular; single.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each <qex>several</qex> ship a victory did gain.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each might his <qex>several</qex> province well command,⟦br⟧
Would all but stoop to what they understand.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Diverse; different; various.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Habits and faculties, <qex>several</qex>, and to be
distinguished.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Four <qex>several</qex> armies to the field are led.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Consisting of a number more than two, but not very
many; divers; sundry; <as>as, <ex>several</ex> persons were present when
the event took place</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Several</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Several
<hw>Sev"er*al</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>By itself; severally.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every kind of thing is laid up <qex>several</qex> in barns or
storehoudses.</q> <rj><qau>Robynson (More's Utopia).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Several</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Several
<hw>Sev"er*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Each particular taken
singly; an item; a detail; an individual.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was not time enough to hear . . . ⟦br⟧
The <qex>severals</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Persons oe objects, more than two, but not very
many.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Several</qex> of them neither rose from any conspicuous
family, nor left any behind them.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An inclosed or separate place; inclosure.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They had their <qex>several</qex> for heathen nations, their
<qex>several</qex> for the people of their own nation.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In several</b></col>, <cd>in a state of separation.</cd>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Where pastures <xex>in several</xex> be.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tusser.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Severality</ent>⟦br⟧
